## <a id="about-pcf"></a> What is <%= vars.product_name_full %>?

<%= vars.first_product_name  %> is a multi-cloud enterprise platform for running, managing, and optimizing distributed apps and workloads.
It offers runtime environments that manage containers using either
Kubernetes or Diego (Cloud Foundry).

The <%= vars.product_name %> platform provides a layer of abstraction that:

- Lets platform operators manage shared resources on one or more cloud infrastructures.
- Hides the complexity of those infrastructures from developers delivering software on the platform.
- Optimizes resource usage and workload uptime.

<%= vars.product_name %> Operators manage the platform and its shared resources by using Ops Manager.  For more information, see [Using Ops Manager](../customizing/ops-man.html).

### <a id="runtimes-services"></a> Runtimes and Services

<%= vars.product_name %> provides runtime environments for managing, hosting, and updating software workloads,
and software services for the hosted workloads to use.

Available runtimes are based on:

- Pivotal Application Service
- Pivotal Container Service (Kubernetes)

See [<%= vars.product_name_full %> Runtimes](../customizing/runtimes.html) for more information about <%= vars.product_name %> runtime environments.

See [<%= vars.product_name_full %> Add-Ons](https://docs.pivotal.io/#add-ons) for all Pivotal platform runtime and service documentation.

